{"lemma":"عُذْرَةٌ","slug":"عُذْرَةٌ","root":"ع.ذ.ر","root_slug":"ع-ذ-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ذ-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["name","noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n28437"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8F%D8%B0%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"virginity"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"excrement, feces"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"an Arab tribe"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n28437","headword_ar":"عُذْرَةٌ","root":"E*r","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"virginity, maidenhead,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hymen;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bakaArapN","text_ar":"بَكَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiD~apN","text_ar":"قِضَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; so called from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea*orN","text_ar":"عَذْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying the “ act of cutting, ” because a girl's hymen ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaAtamu Eu*oratihaA","text_ar":"خَاتَمُ عُذْرَتِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":") is rent when she is devirginated; (Lh, Az, TA;)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEu*orapu","text_ar":"العُذْرَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that whereby a girl is a virgin:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, TA:) [and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu*orN","text_ar":"عُذْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"perhaps signifies the same: (see an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ariymN","text_ar":"اَرِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and see also the next sentence here following:)] pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu*arN","text_ar":"عُذَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Devirgination"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a girl [or woman]: (Lh, K:) [and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu*orN","text_ar":"عُذْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used in the same sense:] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abuw Eu*orihaA","text_ar":"اَبُو عُذْرِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, O, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abw Eu*oratihaA","text_ar":"ابو عُذْرَتِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) (tropical:)  [lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is the father,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the author, of her devirgination"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such a one is he who devirginated her."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, O, K, TA.) And [hence] one says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA AlkalaAmi","text_ar":"هٰذَا الكَلَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa A^abuw Ea*ori","text_ar":"هُوَ اَبُو عَذْرِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was the first utterer of this speech"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA","text_ar":"مَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA AlkalaAmi","text_ar":"هٰذَا الكَلَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anota bi*iY Eu*ori","text_ar":"اَنْتَ بِذِى عُذْرِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou art not the first utterer of this speech."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, TA. [But see an assertion of Sb cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iEorN","text_ar":"شِعْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b3-  And The ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part in the external organs of generation of a girl or woman termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baZor","text_ar":"بَظْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]; (K;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a girl"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"where the operation of circumcision is performed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so called from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea*orN","text_ar":"عَذْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying the “ act of cutting. ” (Lh, Az, TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEaA*uwru","text_ar":"العَاذُورُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b4-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prepuce"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a boy: (O, K:) so accord. to Lh, who does not say whether it be so called before or after it has been cut off: said by others to be the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion of skin which the circumciser cuts off."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Circumcision;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xitaAnN","text_ar":"خِتَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"danaA waqotu Eu*orapi AlS~abiY~i","text_ar":"دَنَا وَقْتُ عُذْرَةِ الصَّبِىِّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The time of the circumcision of the boy drew near."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TK.) ―         -b6-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sign,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mark;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaAmapN","text_ar":"عَلَامَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (O, K, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu*orN","text_ar":"عُذْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei*aArN","text_ar":"عِذَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", last quarter. ―         -b7-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hair upon the withers"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a horse: (S, O, K:) and, (K,) accord. to As, (S, O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a lock,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"small quantity, of hair:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K:) and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naASiyap","text_ar":"نَاصِيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forelock"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a horse]; (K;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hair of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naASiyap","text_ar":"نَاصِيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a horse: (A:) or, accord. to some, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mane"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a horse: (TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu*arN","text_ar":"عُذَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O, TA:) which is said by some to mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hairs"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extending"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the back of the head to the middle of the neck:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and, as pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu*orapN","text_ar":"عُذْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sign, mark,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"token, that is tied to the forelock of a horse that outstrips,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as a preservative"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eye."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 795.) ―         -b8-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEu*orapu","text_ar":"العُذْرَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the appellation of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Five stars at the extremity of the Milky Way:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K:) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"below Sirius, and also called"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEa*aAraY","text_ar":"العَذَارَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the star e of Canis Major"},{"kind":"text","text":"(which is called by our astronomers “ adara, ” often written “ adard, ”)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with four other neighbouring stars,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which rise"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"aurorally"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the midst of the heat:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and, (O, K, TA,) as some say, (O, TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEu*orapu","text_ar":"العُذْرَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a star at the time of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"auroral"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rising of which the heat becomes intense;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, TA;) [app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the star h of Canis Major"},{"kind":"text","text":"(which is called by our astronomers “ aludra ”);]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it rises"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"aurorally, in Central Arabia, in the latter part of July O. S.,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after Sirius and before Canopus, and is accompanied with intense heat, without wind, taking away the breath."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA.) ―         -b9-  Also (i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEu*orapu","text_ar":"العُذْرَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Pain in the fauces,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, K,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"arising"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the blood;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEaA*uwru","text_ar":"العَاذُورُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, accord. to the TA,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEaAduwraA='u","text_ar":"العَادُورَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (thus in some copies of the K, and thus accord. to the CK;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pain of the fauces,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a part near the uvula,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"arising"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the blood:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K:) it is said to be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a small swelling,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pustule, that comes forth in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xarom","text_ar":"خَرْم"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uvula,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as being a"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"projection"},{"kind":"text","text":"from the soft palate,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is between the fauces and the nose: it is incident to children, at the time of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"auroral"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rising of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEu*orap","text_ar":"العُذْرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the star that rises after Sirius, mentioned above; and on the occasion thereof, a woman has recourse to a piece of rag, which she twists tightly, and inserts into the nose so as to pierce that place, whereupon there issues from it black blood, and sometimes it becomes ulcerated;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and this piercing is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~agoru","text_ar":"الدَّغْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": then they suspended to the child some such thing as the [amulet termed]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euw*ap","text_ar":"عُوذَة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA. [See 1 in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dgr","text_ar":"دغر"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b10-  It also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The place of the pain above mentioned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is near the uvula."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","Msb","K","Lh","TA","A","O"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}